_meanings:
{@--1@}
To favour, oblige, treat with 
kindness; {#SilAtalEkadeSamanugfhRAnu vayasyaH#} 
<ls>Ś. 3</ls> our friend will be so good as to,
or kindly, take a seat on the stone;
{#ayaM vizwaro'nugfhyatAM#} <ls>V. 5</ls> be pleased
to sit down &c.; {#maheMdreRa punaranugfhItA#}
<ls>V. 3</ls> favoured (by modifying the
curse); with <ab>instr.</ab> or <ab>abl.</ab> of that
which is an obligation;  
{#anugfhIto'hamanayA maGavataH saMBAvanayA#} <ls>Ś. 6</ls>;  
{#kataratkulamanugfhItaM BagavatyA janmanA#} <ls>K. 135</ls>;
{#anugfhIto'smi ahamupadeSAdBavataH#} <ls>V. 4</ls> I
am much obliged to you &c. ({#anugfhIta#}
is <ab>oft.</ab> used by itself in the sense of
‘much obliged’, ‘many thanks,’ ‘I
thank you’, ‘I esteem it a favour’).

{@--2@} To foster, cherish, protect,
maintain (as fire); {#agnirnityAnugfhItaH#}
{#syAt#} <ls>Āśval.</ls>

{@--5@}
To follow in robbing, seizing or 
depriving.

{@--6@} To keep to, conform or
correspond to, follow, take after;
{#AkftimanugfhRaMti guRAH#} <ls>Vb. 2</ls>;  
{#kzAtraDarmaScAnugfhIto Bavati#} <ls>U. 5.</ls>

To
cause to favour, or to favour;  
{#Aryasya darSanenAtmAnamanugrAhayituM#} <ls>Mu. 4.</ls>
